# Project Doctrine (mandatory)

Read `PROJECT_DOCTRINE.md` and `AGENTS.md` before editing.

## Security

- Deny by default. Policy engine and tool broker authorize; never the model or RAG.
- Schema validation is structure only, not authorization.
- Simulated tools only: no shell, network, credentials, or third-party targets from model output.
- Output filtering and audit logging happen outside the model; redact secrets in logs.
- Human approval for external, destructive, financial, customer-impacting, or permission-changing tools.

## Code quality

- Python 3.12, type hints on all public functions, security-sensitive functions need invariant docstrings.
- No emojis, TODOs in core logic, placeholder controls, eval/exec/pickle on untrusted input, or broad silent except.
- Every control has positive and negative tests; do not skip, xfail, or weaken tests.

## Validation

After substantive changes run: `make validate`, `make demo`, Docker pytest. Do not claim success until all pass.
